's pickup cell you automatically pick it up; if\n     you are on the delivery cell of a parcel you carry, you automatically deliver it.\n- If you are CAUGHT: you keep your parcels, but you are put back on your start cell\n  (5,5) facing N again, the rest of your current plan is cancelled, and the\n  cancelled moves' ticks are forfeited. Standing on a gate cell when it closes is safe.\n\nTHE SCHEDULES (fixed forever; you can compute every future position exactly)\nGate A at (8,3): open exactly when (t mod 6) is in {3, 4, 5}. So it is open at t=3,4,5,9,10,11,... and closed at t=0,1,2,6,7,8,... You can only step ONTO it at a tick t+1 where it is open.\nGuard P: walks a fixed cycle of length 6. Its position at tick t is determined by (t mod 6) as follows: t mod 6=0: (5,2); t mod 6=1: (4,2); t mod 6=2: (3,2); t mod 6=3: (3,1); t mod 6=4: (3,2); t mod 6=5: (4,2). This repeats forever.\nGuard Q: walks a fixed cycle of length 8. Its position at tick t is determined by (t mod 8) as follows: t mod 8=0: (6,1); t mod 8=1: (7,1); t mod 8=2: (8,1); t mod 8=3: (8,2); t mod 8=4: (7,2); t mod 8=5: (8,2); t mod 8=6: (8,1); t mod 8=7: (7,1). This repeats forever.\n\nYOUR JOB\nParcel 1: pick it up at (1,4) (map glyph '1'), deliver it to (6,1) (map glyph 'x'). Pickup and delivery happen automatically when you end a tick on the cell.\nParcel 2: pick it up at (4,8) (map glyph '2'), deliver it to (5,1) (map glyph 'y'). Pickup and delivery happen automatically when you end a tick on the cell.\nDeliver every parcel within 48 ticks. You move by committing to plans of\nexactly 6 moves at a time; you have at most 8 plans in total.\nIf you deliver the last parcel mid-plan, the game ends immediately and the unused\nmoves are discarded.\n\nWORKED EXAMPLE (for the rules only - this is NOT the map above): suppose you are at\n(2,2) facing N at t=0 and want to reach (3,2), which is to the east. Moving F now would\ntake you to (2,1) instead. The correct sequence is R (t=1, now facing E, still at\n(2,2)